The paper deals with joint source-channel coding for multiple access relay channels, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and multimedia (cs.MM) aspects. The use of side information and correlation among sources suggests a possible connection to networked information systems (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the proposed coding schemes involve communication and information theory (cs.CC).
